<h2><strong>6.1 â€“ Common sense approach</strong></h2>
<p>In the previous chapter, we built the Balance Sheet and P&amp;L assumption. Within the P&amp;L assumptions, we dealt with the revenue of the company as well. We did take a rather simplistic approach to estimate the revenue of the company. The approach is ok as long as you intend to build a simple financial model.</p>
<p>However, at times, taking efforts to build a dedicated revenue model of a company pays off.&nbsp; With a dedicated revenue model, you can identify the key revenue drivers and get some granular insights into the behaviour of these revenue drivers.</p>
<p>In this chapter, Iâ€™d like to discuss the approach you need to take while building a companyâ€™s revenue model. As you can imagine, the revenue model sits within the integrated financial model, just like the assumption sheet.</p>
<p>Think of the revenue model as a sub-model within the financial model.</p>
<p>Iâ€™ll take the example of Bajaj auto in this chapter to explain how one can build a companyâ€™s revenue model.</p>
<p>A sensible way to start building a revenue model is by asking common sense questions about the company. In most cases, these questions themselves segways into a template for the revenue model. We will take the same approach to build Bajaj Autoâ€™s revenue model.</p>
<p>So here are a bunch of common-sense questions, and the answers to these questions will help us build the revenue model. &nbsp;By the way, the answers to all the questions are in the companyâ€™s annual report.</p>
<p>So let us start.</p>
<h2><strong>6.2 â€“ Digging data</strong></h2>
<p>As a first step, I download the latest annual report (FY 2020-21) from Bajaj Autoâ€™s website. Iâ€™d suggest you do the same. Like I mentioned, the annual report is where you will find all the information youâ€™d need.</p>
<p><a href="https://zerodha.com/varsity/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/M13-C6-Web.png"><img alt="" class="aligncenter wp-image-10096" height="371" sizes="(max-width: 504px) 100vw, 504px" src="https://zerodha.com/varsity/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/M13-C6-Web-300x221.png" srcset="https://zerodha.com/varsity/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/M13-C6-Web-300x221.png 300w, https://zerodha.com/varsity/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/M13-C6-Web-768x566.png 768w, https://zerodha.com/varsity/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/M13-C6-Web.png 800w" width="504"/></a></p>
<p>Usually, from my experience, as the company matures, the annual report also evolves and provides you with all the necessary information youâ€™d need.</p>
<p>Anyway, let us get started with our common sense QnA. We will begin with a fundamental question.</p>
<p><span style="color: #993300;"><em><strong>What does Bajaj Auto do?</strong></em></span></p>
<p>No brainer, we have seen Bajaj Autoâ€™s bikes and autorickshaws flood the Indian streets. So it is evident that Bajaj manufactures and sells 2 and 3 wheelers. We will cross-check our assumption from the annual report as well.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><a href="https://zerodha.com/varsity/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/Image-1_bikes.png"><img alt="" class="wp-image-10075 aligncenter" height="244" loading="lazy" sizes="(max-width: 452px) 100vw, 452px" src="https://zerodha.com/varsity/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/Image-1_bikes-300x162.png" srcset="https://zerodha.com/varsity/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/Image-1_bikes-300x162.png 300w, https://zerodha.com/varsity/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/Image-1_bikes.png 684w" width="452"/></a></p>
<p>From their annual report, we can see that our assumption is correct (image above if from the annual report). Bajaj does manufacture bikes and autorickshaws. The bikes are further segregated into different segments.</p>
<p>The image below shows the â€˜sports segmentâ€™ or â€™S segmentâ€™ bikes. Apart from the S segment, Bajaj has the Milage or M segment, Supersport or SS segment, Pro biking segment, and scooters.</p>
<p>But the point is Bajaj manufacturesâ€™ bikesâ€™ or two-wheelers, so let us stick to that for now and ignore the segmentation of bikes.</p>
<p>Apart from bikes, they also manufacture autorickshawsâ€™ Commerical Vehiclesâ€™ (CV) or the three-wheeler segment.</p>
<p><a href="https://zerodha.com/varsity/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/Image-2_cv.png"><img alt="" class="aligncenter wp-image-10076" height="171" loading="lazy" sizes="(max-width: 498px) 100vw, 498px" src="https://zerodha.com/varsity/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/Image-2_cv-300x103.png" srcset="https://zerodha.com/varsity/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/Image-2_cv-300x103.png 300w, https://zerodha.com/varsity/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/Image-2_cv.png 685w" width="498"/></a></p>
<p>The CV category has different segments: passenger carrier (good old autorickshaws) and goods carrier.</p>
<p>Why are the segments important to a revenue model?</p>
<p>Well, if you know the segments within a category, you can also figure out the segment-wise revenue.</p>
<p>For example, the S segment is a segment within the bikes category, it will interesting to understand how much revenue they make segment-wise, and which are their popular segments, and what drives these segments.</p>
<p>With this information, you can build a granular revenue model. Unfortunately, the segment-wise revenue distribution is not available in the annual report. Hence we will consider revenue for the entire category as a whole, i.e. the two-wheeler (bikes) and the commercial vehicle (3 wheelers).</p>
<p><em><span style="color: #993300;"><strong>How much does Bajaj Auto manufacture?</strong></span></em></p>
<p>I suppose this is also a straightforward question. As a financial modeller (or even an investor), you need to understand the manufacturing capacity of the company. The reason is simple.</p>
<p>Suppose they manufacture 100 bikes in the year, and if they are selling 60 bikes, then with this information we can interpret the following â€“</p>
<ul>
<li style="list-style-type: none;">
<ul>
<li style="list-style-type: none;">
<ul>
<li>The manufacturing plant operates at 60% capacity utilization. Capacity utilization is a simple ratio of how much they sell versus how much they manufacture.</li>
<li>The company has enough manufacturing buffer to meet future demands</li>
<li>The company is unlikely to spend more money in terms of CAPEX anytime soon</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
<p>Other perspectives â€“</p>
<ul>
<li style="list-style-type: none;">
<ul>
<li style="list-style-type: none;">
<ul>
<li>Why is the company selling only 60?</li>
<li>How much do their competitors sell?</li>
<li>Where does the company stand in terms of competition?</li>
<li>How big is the industry? How many bikes (across all companies) are sold in a year?</li>
<li>What is the companyâ€™s market share? (company sales divided/industry sales)</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
<p>These questions will help us size up the company and eventually help the investors in the valuation process.</p>
<p>Anyway, we will get back to the revenue model.&nbsp; I found this image in their annual report interesting â€“</p>
<p><a href="https://zerodha.com/varsity/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/Image-3_loc.png"><img alt="" class="aligncenter wp-image-10077" height="360" loading="lazy" sizes="(max-width: 501px) 100vw, 501px" src="https://zerodha.com/varsity/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/Image-3_loc-300x216.png" srcset="https://zerodha.com/varsity/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/Image-3_loc-300x216.png 300w, https://zerodha.com/varsity/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/Image-3_loc.png 729w" width="501"/></a></p>
<p>The image gives us all the information in one shot. Let me list down the information for you â€“</p>
<ul>
<li style="list-style-type: none;">
<ul>
<li style="list-style-type: none;">
<ul>
<li>The company has three manufacturing units (or plants) in India, located in â€“ Pantnagar, Waluj, and Chakan.</li>
<li>Waluj is the oldest plant (set up in 1984), while the Pantnagar plant is their newest.</li>
<li>All plants have been operational for a long time now.</li>
<li>Pantnagar plant has a production capacity to manufacture 1.8M bikes, no commercial vehicles here.</li>
<li>Waluj plant has a production capacity to manufacture 2.4M bikes and 9.3L commercial vehicles. Waluj is a super important plant for Bajaj auto since this plant has production of both categories plus this is the only plant to manufacture commercial vehicles.</li>
<li>Chakan plant has a production capacity to manufacture 1.2M units of bikes.</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
<p>Since all the manufacturing facilities are old enough, assuming that the company has had a similar production capacity for the last few years is fair.</p>
