<h3><strong>Key takeaways from this chapter </strong></h3>
<ul>
<li style="list-style-type: none;">
<ul>
<li>The revenue model is a sub-model within your primary model</li>
<li>You can build complex revenue models by starting with simple common sense questions</li>
<li>All the data needed to make a revenue model is usually available in the annual report of the company</li>
<li>Use the revenue model to extract other information like capacity utilization, CAPEX cycles, and industry market share.</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
